        <div class="flip-box-back">
            <h1>PROJECTS</h1>
            <!-- projects -->
            <div class="project-container">
                <div class="card bg-light
                 text-white" style="width: 30rem;">
                    <img class="card-img" src="/public/images/projects/portfolio.JPG" alt="Card image">
                    <div class="card-img-overlay" onclick="">
                        <div class="project-link-container">
                            <h5 class="card-title"> Portfolio </h5>
                        </div>
                        <p class=" card-text">This is the portfolio project that you are viewing. I like to
                            highlight this project because
                            it was created with the idea of a SPA in mind using node as the backend. This app
                            uses a color scheme that doesn't distract from the portfolio. It Is a fully
                            responsive clean layout.</p>
                        <p class="card-text">Tools Used: JavaScript, Node, express, HTML5, CSS3, and Hosted
                            on Heroku</p>
                        <p class="link-to-project" rel="noreferrer"><a href="#">PROJECT</a></p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="card-space"></div>
                <div class="card bg-light text-white" style="width: 30rem;">
                    <img class="card-img" src="public\images\projects\cartender.png" alt="Card image">
                    <div class="card-img-overlay" onclick="">
                        <div class="project-link-container">
                            <h5 class="card-title">CARtender</h5>
                        </div>
                        <p class=" card-text">CARtender is a web application that helps organize your automotive maintenance and other miscellaneous tasks. Track the dates and mileage of oil changes, tire changes and other repairs and set up reminders so you never forget them again.</p>
                        <p>My role on this project included The logic for the garage page and map page, Creating and connecting the sequelize database to the front-end</p>
                        <p class="card-text">Tools Used: jQuery, HTML5, CSS3, Nodejs, Passport, Sequelize, and ARCGIS Mapping API</p>
                        <p class="link-to-project"><a href="https://car-tender.herokuapp.com/" rel="noreferrer">PROJECT</a></p>
                        <p class="link-to-project"><a href="https://github.com/erynjohn/cartender" rel="noreferrer">CODE</a></p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="card-space"></div>
                <div class="card bg-light text-white" style="width: 30rem;">
                    <img class="card-img" src="/public/images/projects/burger_display.png" alt="Card image" width="100%">
                    <div class="card-img-overlay" onclick="">
                        <div class="project-link-container">
                            <h5 class="card-title"> Da Burger Shop </h5>
                        </div>
                        <p class=" card-text">This project lets you create new burgers and add favorite burgers to your
                            favorites list using MySQL to persist user entries over different sessions. Handlebars
                            handle the template that the data is being fed into. This app is completely responsive and
                            can easily be used on mobile devices. New features coming soon.</p>
                        <p class="card-text">Tools Used: jQuery, Node, express, Handlebars, CSS3, MySQL, JawsDB, and
                            Hosted on Heroku.</p>
                        <p class="link-to-project"><a href="https://da-burger-shop.herokuapp.com/" rel="noreferrer">Project</a></p>
                        <p class="link-to-project"><a href="https://github.com/erynjohn/da-burger" rel="noreferrer">Code</a></p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="card-space"></div>
                <div class="card bg-light text-white" style="width: 30rem;">
                    <img class="card-img" src="/public/images/projects/train-times.JPG" alt="Card image">
                    <div class="card-img-overlay" onclick="">
                        <div class="project-link-container">
                            <h5 class="card-title">Train Schedule 2.0</h5>
                        </div>
                        <p class=" card-text">This project is a scheduling system that takes the train name,
                            destination, and frequency. It
                            then populates a dynamically created table with the updated train name,
                            destination, and time remaining until the next train arrives. </p>
                        <p class="card-text">Tools Used: jQuery, HTML5, CSS3, Moment.js</p>
                        <p class="link-to-project"><a href="https://erynjohn.github.io/train-times" rel="noreferrer">PROJECT</a></p>
                        <p class="link-to-project"><a href="https://github.com/erynjohn/train-times" rel="noreferrer">CODE</a></p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="card-space"></div>
                <div class="card bg-light text-white" style="width: 30rem;">
                    <img class="card-img" src="/public/images/projects/destinair.jpg" alt="Card image">
                    <div class="card-img-overlay" onclick="">
                        <div class="project-link-container">
                            <h5 class="card-title">Destin-Air</h5>
                        </div>
                        <p class=" card-text">This project is a collaborative effort working as part of a team. My
                            role on this project inculeded rendering dynamically created index cards
                            along with the current weather for the target city and implemented the login logic allowing for improved data of
                            current site usage.</p>
                        <p class="card-text">Tools Used: jQuery, HTML5, CSS3, Firebase, and Ajax</p>
                        <p class="link-to-project"><a href="https://erynjohn.github.io/Destn-Air" rel="noreferrer">PROJECT</a></p>
                        <p class="link-to-project"><a href="https://github.com/erynjohn/Destn-Air" rel="noreferrer">CODE</a></p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="card-space"></div>
                <div class="card bg-light text-white" style="width: 30rem;">
                    <img class="card-img" src="/public/images/projects/bamazon.JPG" alt="Card image">
                    <div class="card-img-overlay" onclick="">
                        <div class="project-link-container">
                            <h5 class="card-title">Bamazon For Everyone</h5>
                        </div>
                        <p class=" card-text">This project uses the CLI and Node to query a MySQL database. Inquirer was
                            used to providing prompts for the user to purchase items from the database and have the
                            table reflect the results. CLI-Table makes results look a little more user-friendly</p>
                        <p class="card-text">Tools Used: Node.js, MySQL, Inquirer, CLI-Table</p>
                        <p class="link-to-project"><a href="https://github.com/erynjohn/bamazon" rel="noreferrer">CODE</a></p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            {{> footer}}
        </div>
        <div class="flip-box-back-X">
            <h1>CONTACT</h1>
            <!-- contact -->
            <div class="contact-container">
                <form method="POST" action="send">
                    <div class="form-group">
                        <label for="name">NAME</label>
                        <input type="text" class="form-control" id="name" aria-describedby="name"
                            placeholder="JOHN SMITH" name="name" aria-label="Enter name">
                    </div>
                    <div class="form-group">
                        <label for="email">EMAIL ADDRESS</label>
                        <input type="email" class="form-control" id="email" aria-describedby="email"
                            placeholder="johnsmith@gmail.com" name="email" aria-label="Enter email address">
                    </div>
                    <div class="form-group">
                        <label for="company">COMPANY</label>
                        <input type="text" class="form-control" id="company" placeholder="XYZ COMPANY" name="company"
                            aria-label="Enter company name">
                    </div>
                    <div class="form-group">
                        <label for="message" m>MESSAGE</label>
                        <textarea class="form-control" id="message" rows="4" placeholder="ENTER MESSAGE HERE..."
                            name="message" aria-label="Enter message"></textarea>
                    </div>
                    <button type="submit" class="btn btn-outline-warning btn-block btn-dark">Send</button>

                </form>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>